This paper deals with improving machine translation using information about the structure of documents, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of neural networks in this work suggests that it may fall under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of side constraints and cache-based models suggests that it may also fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The fact that the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV) through the use of parallel corpora from Wikipedia biographies also suggests that it may fall under those sub-categories.
